abstract: The main union representing employees at The Wall Street Journal and the newspaper’s parent have reached a tentative agreement on a three-year contract.
snippet: The main union representing employees at The Wall Street Journal and the newspaper’s parent have reached a tentative agreement on a three-year contract.
lead_paragraph: The main union representing employees at The Wall Street Journal and the newspaper’s parent, Dow Jones & Company, have reached a tentative agreement on a three-year contract, union officials said last night.

headline.main: Tentative Deal Reached With Union at Dow Jones
headline.print_headline: Tentative Deal Reached With Union at Dow Jones

abstract: The planned initial public offering of Virgin Radio by its owner, SMG, is unlikely to proceed this year, Dow Jones Newswires reported.

headline.main: Virgin Radio I.P.O. May Not Happen This Year, Report Says
